# .gitignore — repository hygiene + data governance policy.
#
# This repository is NOT yet under git (see ReClass Model/docs/data_governance.md).
# This file is forward-looking: it activates the moment `git init` is run. The
# committable vs regenerable/local policy it encodes is mirrored by the commit guard
# `ReClass Model/ops/repo_guard.py` and documented in docs/data_governance.md.
#
# Rule of thumb:
#   * COMMIT: source code, docs/READMEs, small benchmark fixtures, source checksums.
#   * IGNORE: large raw source data, reference genomes, provider caches, and every
#             regenerable artifact (plots, validation reports, enriched copies).

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
# Python
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
# Virtual environments
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
.venv/
.venv-*/
venv/
env/

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
# OS / editor cruft
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
# Reference genome FASTA cache (multi-GB; NEVER commit). Keep only the README.
# These patterns are global so a FASTA dropped anywhere is caught.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
*.fa
*.fasta
*.fai
*.2bit
ReClass Model/data/reference/*
!ReClass Model/data/reference/README.md

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
# Raw, local-only source data (large public downloads; NEVER commit).
# Keep the README and the upstream checksums so the snapshot is reproducible.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
ReClass Model/data/raw/*
!ReClass Model/data/raw/README.md
!ReClass Model/data/raw/*.md5

# Common bulk archive / genomics file shapes, wherever they appear.
*.zip
*.gz
*.bgz
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.vcf
*.vcf.gz
*.bcf
*.bam
*.cram

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
# Provider caches (regenerable from public sources via ingest/*). Keep README.
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
ReClass Model/data/cache/providers/*
!ReClass Model/data/cache/providers/README.md

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
# Generated, regenerable artifacts (NOT source of business logic).
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
plots/
ReClass Model/validation/reports/

# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
# Private / clinical data — must NEVER be committed (defense in depth; the
# clinical schema lives in PostgreSQL, not in the repo).
# --------------------------------------------------------------------------- #
**/data/private/
*.phi
*.phi.json
*_patient*.csv
*_mrn*.csv

# Committed ON PURPOSE (small benchmark snapshots; see docs/data_governance.md):
#   ReClass Model/validation/fixtures/*.json  -> tracked, not ignored.
